          <li>Players are strongly encouraged to maintain personal health and accident insurance.</li>
          <li>MPA does not provide insurance coverage for individual players.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>9. Disciplinary Actions</h2>
        <h3>9.1 Violations</h3>
        <p>MPA may take disciplinary action for violations including but not limited to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Breach of code of conduct</li>
          <li>Unsportsmanlike behavior</li>
          <li>Violation of anti-doping policies</li>
          <li>Providing false information</li>
          <li>Failure to comply with MPA rules and regulations</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>9.2 Penalties</h3>
        <p>Disciplinary actions may include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Warning or reprimand</li>
          <li>Temporary suspension from tournaments</li>
          <li>Permanent ban from MPA activities</li>
          <li>Termination of membership</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>10. Amendments and Updates</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>MPA reserves the right to modify these Terms and Conditions at any time.</li>
          <li>Players will be notified of significant changes via email or website announcement.</li>
          <li>Continued participation after changes constitutes acceptance of new terms.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>11. Termination</h2>
        <h3>11.1 Voluntary Termination</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Players may terminate their membership at any time by contacting MPA.</li>
          <li>Termination does not entitle players to refunds of any fees paid.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>11.2 Involuntary Termination</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>MPA may terminate membership for violations of these terms.</li>
          <li>Terminated players may appeal the decision through established procedures.</li>
        </ul>

